an football|P}}\n\n| reserve_lists =\n\n| practice_squad =\n}}\n\n==Regular season==\n\n===Schedule===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-style=\"background:black;color:#BB8C3C;\"\n! Week\n! Date\n! Opponent\n! Result\n! Attendance\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 1\n| September 13, 1987\n| [[1987 Cleveland Browns season|Cleveland Browns]]\n| W 28\u201321\n| <center>59,900</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 2\n| September 20, 1987\n| at [[1987 Philadelphia Eagles season|Philadelphia Eagles]]\n| L 27\u201321\n| <center>57,485</center>\n|-style=\"background:\"\n| \u2013\n| September 27, 1987\n| [[1987 Atlanta Falcons season|Atlanta Falcons]]\n| canceled\n| \n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 3\n| October 4, 1987\n| [[1987 Los Angeles Rams season|Los Angeles Rams]]\n| W 37\u201310\n| <center>29,745</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 4\n| October 11, 1987\n| at [[1987 St. Louis Cardinals (NFL) season|St. Louis Cardinals]]\n| L 24\u201319\n| <center>11,795</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 5\n| October 18, 1987\n| at [[1987 Chicago Bears season|Chicago Bears]]\n| W 19\u201317\n| <center>46,813</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ffdddd;\"\n| 6\n| October 25, 1987\n| [[1987 San Francisco 49ers season|San Francisco 49ers]]\n| L 24\u201322\n| <center>60,497</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 7\n| November 1, 1987\n| at [[1987 Atlanta Falcons season|Atlanta Falcons]]\n| W 38\u20130\n| <center>42,196</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 8\n| November 8, 1987\n| at [[1987 Los Angeles Rams season|Los Angeles Rams]]\n| W 31\u201314\n| <center>43,379</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 9\n| November 15, 1987\n| at [[1987 San Francisco 49ers season|San Francisco 49ers]]\n| W 26\u201324\n| <center>60,436</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 10\n| November 22, 1987\n| [[1987 New York Giants season|New York Giants]]\n| W 23\u201314\n| <center>67,639</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 11\n| November 29, 1987\n| at [[1987 Pittsburgh Steelers season|Pittsburgh Steelers]]\n| W 20\u201316\n| <center>47,896</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 12\n| December 6, 1987\n| [[1987 Tampa Bay Buccaneers season|Tampa Bay Buccaneers]]\n| W 44\u201334\n| <center>66,471</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 13\n| December 13, 1987\n| [[1987 Houston Oilers season|Houston Oilers]]\n| W 24\u201310\n| <center>68,257</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 14\n| December 20, 1987\n| at [[1987 Cincinnati Bengals season|Cincinnati Bengals]]\n| W 41\u201324\n| <center>43,424</center>\n|-style=\"background: #ddffdd;\"\n| 15\n| December 27, 1987\n| [[1987 Green Bay Packers season|Green Bay Packers]]\n| W 33\u201324\n| <center>68,364</center>\n|}\n\n===Standings===\n{{1987 NFC West standings}}\n\n==Playoffs==\n\n===NFC Wild Card Game===\n{{Americanfootballbox | title=Minnesota Vikings 44, New Orleans Saints 10\n|Road='''Vikings'''\n|R1=10\n|R2=21\n|R3=3\n|R4=10\n|RT=44\n|Home=Saints\n|H1=7\n|H2=3\n|H3=0\n|H4=0\n|HT=10\n|stadium= [[Louisiana Superdome]], [[New Orleans]]\n|time= 12:30 p.m. [[Eastern Time Zone|EST]]/11:30 a.m. [[Central Time Zone|CST]]\n|TV=[[NFL on CBS|CBS]]\n|TVAnnouncers= [[Pat Summerall]] and [[John Madden (football)|John Madden]]\n|attendance= 68,127\n}}\nIn the Saints' first playoff game in history, the Vikings dominated the game by recording two sacks, forcing four turnovers, and allowing only 149 yards. [[Anthony Carter (American football)|Anthony Carter]] returned a punt for a touchdown, and future Saints quarterback [[Wade Wilson (American football)|Wade Wilson]] threw a Hail Mary pass for a touchdown to [[Hassan Jones]] on the last play of the first half.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.pro-football-reference.com/teams/nor/1987.htm 1987 New Orleans Saints] at [[Pro-Football-Reference.com]]\n\n{{New Orleans Saints}}\n{{New Orleans Saints seasons}}\n{{1987 NFL season by team}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1987 New Orleans Saints season}}\n[[Category:1987 National Football League season by team|New Orleans]]\n[[Category:New Orleans Saints seasons]]\n[[Category:1987 in sports in Louisiana|New]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NFL season\n| team            = New Orleans Saints\n| year            = 1987\n| record          = 12\u20133\n| division_place  = 2nd [[NFC West]]\n| coach           = [[Jim E. Mora|Jim Mora]]\n| general manager = [[Jim Finks]]\n| owner           = [[Tom Benson]]\n| stadium         = [[Louisiana Superdome]]\n| playoffs        = Lost [[1987\u201388 NFL playoffs|Wild Card playoffs]] ([[1987 Minnesota Vikings season|Vikings]]) 10\u201344\n| pro_bowlers     = G [[Brad Edelman]] <br/>T [[Hoby Brenner]]<br/>RB [[Reuben Mayes]]<br/>LB [[Sam Mills]]<br/> CB [[Dave Waymer]]<br/>K [[Morten Andersen]]\n| shortnavlink    = Saints seasons\n}}\n\nThe '''1987 New Orleans Saints season''' was the team's 21st year in the [[National Football League]] (NFL). The [[1987 NFL strike|strike-shortened]] year was the Saints' first-ever winning season. The Saints also qualified for the postseason for the first time, riding largely on a nine-game winning streak to close the season. The Saints earned the second-best record in the NFL in 1987, but were in the same division as the team with the best record, [[1987 San Francisco 49ers season|the San Francisco 49ers]], and entered the playoffs as a wild card. However, they were soundly defeated at home by [[1987 Minnesota Vikings season|the Minnesota Vikings]] in the Wild Card round of the [[1987\u201388 NFL playoffs|playoffs]], by a score of 44\u201310. The Vikings entered the playoffs with an 8\u20137 record and needed the Dallas Cowboys to defeat the St. Louis Cardinals on the final day of the season to qualify. The Saints' first winning season would be followed by another six consecutive non-losing seasons. Before the 1987 season, the Saints' non-losing seasons had consisted of only two 8\u20138 seasons, in [[1979 New Orleans Saints season|1979]] and [[1983 New Orleans Saints season|1983]]. Head coach [[Jim E. Mora|Jim Mora]] was named [[NFL Coach of the Year]].\n\n==Offseason==\n\n===NFL Draft===\n{{main article|1987 NFL Draft}}\n{{NFL team draft start\n | year     = 1987\n | teamname = New Orleans Saints\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 1\n | pick       = 11\n | player     = [[Shawn Knight]]\n | position   = [[Defensive end]]\n | college    = [[1986 BYU Cougars football team|BYU]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 2\n | pick       = 40\n | player     = [[Lonzell Hill]]\n | position   = [[Wide receiver]]\n | college    = [[1986 Washington Huskies football team|Washington]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 3\n | pick       = 67\n | player     = Michael Adams\n | position   = [[Defensive back]]\n | college    = [[Arkansas State Red Wolves football|Arkansas State]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 4\n | pick       = 96\n | player     = [[Steve Trapilo]]\n | position   = [[Guard (American and Canadian football)|Guard]]\n | college    = [[1986 Boston College Eagles football team|Boston College]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 5\n | pick       = 123\n | player     = [[Milton Mack]]\n | position   = Defensive back\n | college    = [[Alcorn State Braves football|Alcorn State]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 6\n | pick       = 152\n | player     = Thomas Henley\n | position   = Wide receiver\n | college    = [[1986 Stanford Cardinal football team|Stanford]]\n | notes      = \n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 7\n | pick       = 179\n | player     = [[Gene Atkins]]\n | position   = Defensive back\n | college    = [[Florida A&M Rattlers football|Florida A&M]]\n | notes      = \n | maderoster = yes\n}}\n{{NFL team draft entry\n | round      = 8\