{"title_page": "1983 USFL Draft", "text_new": "{{Infobox sports draft\n| name          = 1983 USFL Draft\n| logo          = \n| logosize      = \n| logoalt       = \n| image         = \n| imagesize     = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| date          = January 4, 1983\n| time          = \n| location      = [[Grand Hyatt New York|Grand Hyatt Hotel]], New York\n| network       = \n| sponsor       = \n| league        = [[United States Football League|USFL]]\n| first         = [[Dan Marino]], QB<br>[[Los Angeles Express (USFL)|Los Angeles Express]]\n| first_round   =\n| fewnum        = \n| fewest        = \n| mostnum       = \n| most          = \n| overall       = 288\n| rounds        = 24\n| prev          = \n| next          = [[1984 USFL Draft|1984]]  \n}}\n\nThe [[1983 USFL season|1983]] USFL Draft was the first [[USFL Collegiate Draft|Collegiate Draft]] of the [[United States Football League]] (USFL). It took place on January 4, 1983, at the [[Grand Hyatt New York|Grand Hyatt Hotel]] in New York.\n\n==Player selections==\n{|\n|-\n|style=\"background-color:#FFCC00; border:1px solid #aaaaaa; width:2em;\"|\n|= [[All-Star]]\n|-\n|style=\"background-color:lightsteelblue; border:1px solid #aaaaaa; width:2em;\"|\n|= USFL MVP\n|}\n\n<!-- The Team names, player positions, and college names should only be linked the first time they appear in the entire page -->\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable sortable\" style=\"width: 100%\"\n|-\n! Round !! Pick # !! USFL Team  !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n| 1 || 1 || [[Los Angeles Express (USFL)|Los Angeles Express]]|| [[Dan Marino]] || [[Quarterback]] || [[University of Pittsburgh|Pittsburgh]]\n|-\n| 1 || 2 || [[Chicago Blitz]]|| [[Tim Spencer (American football)|Tim Spencer]] || [[Running back]] || [[Ohio State University|Ohio State]]\n|-\n| 1 || 3 || [[Birmingham Stallions]]|| [[Reggie Collier]] || [[Quarterback]] || [[University of Southern Mississippi|Southern Mississippi]]\n|-\n| 1 || 4 || [[Washington Federals]]|| [[